                &lt;span class=&quot;comment-copy&quot;&gt;I keep coming back to this post despite being a Python veteran. The main message for me is: Either fiddle around with &lt;code&gt;sys.path&lt;/code&gt; and &lt;code&gt;__package__&lt;/code&gt; (which is rather ugly, see the other answers) or simply create a &quot;main script&quot; &lt;code&gt;main.py&lt;/code&gt; in the root directory of your project and put all modules to be imported in subdirectories. &lt;code&gt;main.py&lt;/code&gt; can then access all modules directly through their package names (= the names of the respective folders they&apos;re in).&lt;/span&gt;

