            &lt;div class=&quot;comment-body js-comment-edit-hide&quot;&gt;

                &lt;span class=&quot;comment-copy&quot;&gt;This answer is currently off on a few important details regarding &lt;code&gt;__name__&lt;/code&gt; and &lt;code&gt;sys.path&lt;/code&gt;. Specifically, with &lt;code&gt;python -m pkg.mod&lt;/code&gt;, &lt;code&gt;__name__&lt;/code&gt; is set to &lt;code&gt;__main__&lt;/code&gt;, not &lt;code&gt;pkg.mod&lt;/code&gt;; relative imports are resolved using &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.python.org/dev/peps/pep-0366/#proposed-change&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noreferrer&quot;&gt;&lt;code&gt;__package__&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/a&gt; rather than &lt;code&gt;__name__&lt;/code&gt; in this case. Also, Python adds the script&apos;s directory rather than the current directory to &lt;code&gt;sys.path&lt;/code&gt; when running &lt;code&gt;python path/to/script.py&lt;/code&gt;; it adds the current directory to &lt;code&gt;sys.path&lt;/code&gt; when running most other ways, including &lt;code&gt;python -m pkg.mod&lt;/code&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;

